{
  "texts": [
    "This panel was enriched for difficult-to-treat isolates (78%) 35 and MDR (80%) isolates.",
    "The MIC required to inhibit growth of 90% of these isolates was 1 mg l -1 (MIC 90; range, ≤0.016-4 mg l -1) (Fig. 4a and Supplementary Table 7).",
    "The pharmacokinetic properties of zosurabalpin were examined both in single-dose and multiple-dose pharmacokinetic studies in mice, revealing acceptable plasma exposures after s.c. administration with high clearance (51 ml min -1 kg -1), a low volume of distribution (0.7 l kg -1), a short terminal half-life (0.3 h) and moderate protein binding (fraction unbound, 37%) (Extended Data Table 1).",
    "Zosurabalpin lacked off-target activities in a 50-receptor panel assay, and biotransformation studies found no substantial interactions with the cytochrome P450 system, neither as inhibitor nor inducer (Extended Data Table 1 and Supplementary Table 1).",
    "The physicochemical properties were found to be consistent with those required for clinical antibiotics, for which gram-scale doses are common, including low lipophilicity (distribution coefficient logD 7.4 = -2.46) and high aqueous solubility (>100 mg ml -1 at pH 1-9) 36."
  ]
}